The default setup process on Windows 7 appears to open the firewall to incoming connections, but it only gets halfway. A prompt during installation allows the user to tell Windows Firewall to accept incoming connections to the applications; however, access to the ports does not get set, and accordingly Atlassian applications may not be available on the intranet depending on other settings. If the applications are up and accessible from the installation machine, but not accessible from other machines on the network, the administrator should check to make sure port access to the relevant ports is explicitly enabled in Windows Firewall.

