If a customer creates multiple users with the same email address, the first user created with the email address is used for processing all emails (even if the user is disabled).  If the first user does not have permissions to perform the actions, the message is denied.

Instead, the mail handler should check the remaining users for permissions to perform the function and attempt to do so until the list is exhausted before denying the message.

